hh3cDot11Sa.name: hh3cDot11Sa

revisions.description: The initial revision of this MIB module.

hh3cDot11Sa.contactinfo: Platform Team Hangzhou H3C Tech. Co., Ltd. Hai-Dian District Beijing P.R. China http://www.h3c.com Zip:100085
hh3cDot11Sa.description: This MIB module provides spectrum analysis information. The initial revision of this MIB module. The spectrum analysis module on APs is able to examine the radio frequency (RF) environment in which the Wi-Fi network is operating, identify interference and classify its sources. An analysis of the results can then be used to quickly isolate issues with packet transmission, channel quality, and traffic congestion caused by contention with other devices operating in the same band or channel.

hh3cDot11SaCfgTable.name: hh3cDot11SaCfgTable
hh3cDot11SaCfgTable.description: This table is used to configure spectrum analysis.

hh3cDot11SaCfgEntry.name: hh3cDot11SaCfgEntry
hh3cDot11SaCfgEntry.description: This entry contains the spectrum analysis configuration.

hh3cDot11SaCfgRadioType.name: hh3cDot11SaCfgRadioType
hh3cDot11SaCfgRadioType.description: Represents the radio type of the configuration.

hh3cDot11SaEnable.name: hh3cDot11SaEnable
hh3cDot11SaEnable.description: Represents whether spectrum analysis is enabled globally.

hh3cDot11SaRptDevType.name: hh3cDot11SaRptDevType
hh3cDot11SaRptDevType.description: Represents which types of interference devices should be reported.

hh3cDot11SaTrapDevEnable.name: hh3cDot11SaTrapDevEnable
hh3cDot11SaTrapDevEnable.description: Represents whether the interference device trap is enabled.

hh3cDot11SaTrapDevType.name: hh3cDot11SaTrapDevType
hh3cDot11SaTrapDevType.description: Represents which types of interference device will send traps when the interference device trap is enabled.

hh3cDot11SaTrapAQEnable.name: hh3cDot11SaTrapAQEnable
hh3cDot11SaTrapAQEnable.description: Represents whether the air quality trap is enabled.

hh3cDot11SaTrapAQThreshold.name: hh3cDot11SaTrapAQThreshold
hh3cDot11SaTrapAQThreshold.description: Represents the air quality trap threshold. When the air quality is below this value, the air quality trap will be sent.

hh3cDot11SaDrivenRRMEnable.name: hh3cDot11SaDrivenRRMEnable
hh3cDot11SaDrivenRRMEnable.description: Configure whether to trigger RRM to run when an access point detects a certain level of interference.

hh3cDot11SaDrivenRRMSnt.name: hh3cDot11SaDrivenRRMSnt
hh3cDot11SaDrivenRRMSnt.description: Configure the threshold at which RRM will be triggered. When the interference level for the access point rises above the threshold level, RRM initiates a local dynamic channel assignment (DCA) run and changes the channel of the affected access point radio if possible to improve network performance. Low represents a decreased sensitivity to changes in the environment while high represents an increased sensitivity.

hh3cDot11SaRtFFTDataTable.name: hh3cDot11SaRtFFTDataTable
hh3cDot11SaRtFFTDataTable.description: This table contains the real-time FFT data for spectrum analysis.

hh3cDot11SaRtFFTDataEntry.name: hh3cDot11SaRtFFTDataEntry
hh3cDot11SaRtFFTDataEntry.description: This entry contains the real-time FFT data for spectrum analysis.
